import numpy as np
from scipy.ndimage import gaussian_filter1d

# Generate some sample time series data
time = np.linspace(0, 10, 100)
data = np.sin(time) + np.random.normal(0, 0.1, size=100)

# Set the standard deviation for the Gaussian kernel
sigma = 2.0

# Apply Gaussian convolution using NumPy's gaussian_filter1d function
smoothed_data = gaussian_filter1d(data, sigma)

# Print the original and smoothed data
print("Original Data:")
print(data)
print("\nSmoothed Data:")
print(smoothed_data)

plt.plot(data)
